					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Pretty cool use of parallax effects! The fact that you have to design levels in stripes really limits what you can do layout-wise though.
<br />
<br />The splits are indeed looking kinda glitchy at this point... You might have to time the scroll changes better so that they always happen during HBlank.
<br />
<br />The illusion of 2 scrolling layers really makes it look like a 16-bit game. If you used other common tricks such as layering sprites (or at least combining sprites with different palettes to form meta-sprites) to increase the amount of colors per meta-sprite you could fool a lot of people.
<br />
<br />The physics could be improved a bit, although it looks similar to what was used in early 16-bit games.</div>

